version_description: The name of this song has been taken straight from the soundtrack's listing. The strumming pattern for this song, which is relatively easy to play, is key for the sound and feel of the song. If you watch the youtube video for this clip, it will help a great deal.
There is very little guitar noise during verse...just palm-mute E. Also, E-D words in place of the main riff he plays if you get the rhythm correct.
Includes guitar solo and piano chords.
This version does not use simplified chords for ease of play. It also contains the root note of chords in some instances to help with correct chromatic movement.
